# Main functions

---

## 1. Find node by ID

```js
function getNode(id) {
  for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
    if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
  }
  return null;
}
```

---

## 2. Physics update

This is the core.

### A. Pairwise repulsion between every node pair

```js
for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
  for (let j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
    const dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
    const dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
    const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
    const force = config.repulsion / (dist * dist);

    const fx = dx / dist * force;
    const fy = dy / dist * force;

    nodes[i].vx += fx;
    nodes[i].vy += fy;
    nodes[j].vx -= fx;
    nodes[j].vy -= fy;
  }
}
```

This pushes all nodes away from each other with an inverse-square force.

---

### B. Spring forces along links

```js
for (let i = 0; i < links.length; i++) {
  const na = getNode(links[i].a);
  const nb = getNode(links[i].b);
  if (!na || !nb) continue;

  const dx = nb.x - na.x;
  const dy = nb.y - na.y;
  const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;

  const stretch = dist - links[i].rest;
  const force = (links[i].k || config.springForce) * stretch;

  na.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
  na.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
  nb.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
  nb.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
}
```

This pulls connected nodes together if too far apart, and pushes them apart if too close.

---

### C. Damping + weak center attraction + integrate velocity

```js
for (let i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
  nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.centance;
  nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.centance;

  nodes[i].vx *= config.damping;
  nodes[i].vy *= config.damping;

  nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
  nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
}
```

This:
- gently pulls everything toward `(400, 300)`
- damps velocity so motion settles instead of exploding
- updates positions

---

## 3. Spawn particles

Every 3 ticks, if particle count is below the max, it creates one particle at a random node.

```js
function spawnParticle() {
  if (particles.length >= config.particles) return;

  const node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
  const angle = Math.random() * TAU;
  const speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT1_2;

  particles.push({
    x: node.x,
    y: node.y,
    vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
    vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
    age: 0,
    maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
    size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * PHI * SQRT1_2)
  });
}
```

So particles drift away from nodes in random directions and have random lifetimes/sizes.

---

## 4. Update particles

```js
function updateParticles() {
  for (let i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
    const p = particles[i];

    p.vx *= (1 - config.attenuation * 0.125);
    p.vy *= (1 - config.attenuation * 0.125);

    p.x += p.vx;
    p.y += p.vy;
    p.age++;

    if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
      particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
  }
}
```

Particles slow down gradually and are deleted once too old.

---

## 5. Interpolate view toward target

```js
function updateView() {
  view.x += (targetView.x - view.x) * config.phase;
  view.y += (targetView.y - view.y) * config.phase;
  view.scale += (targetView.scale - view.scale) * config.phase;
}
```

Again, in this snippet `targetView` never changes.

---

## 6. Main loop

```js
function tickFrame() {
  updatePhysics();
  updateParticles();
  updateView();

  if (tick % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
  tick++;
}

setInterval(tickFrame, 16);
```

Runs every 16 ms.

